<subSubSection id="681166BE5509E7976279E636AC77AC7A" pageId="0" pageNumber="73" type="conservation status">
<paragraph id="8830B55B78DAE59F890D3476E6D50430" pageId="0" pageNumber="73">Conservation status.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1C9B2E15E41F32CDB1041E7AAD6BF013" pageId="0" pageNumber="73">
Critically Endangered (CR). We found around ten individuals of 
<taxonomicName id="A7FF87E0FEA4DD77C5BC520A884B9810" genus="L." lsidName="L. congtroiensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="73" rank="species" species="congtroiensis">
<emphasis id="AD58C30616C3812D8523DBB0392B6AD9" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="73">L. congtroiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
along the road and inside the permanent plot at Cong Troi area, and three individuals in Mt. Langbiang, both located inside the protected area of Bidoup-Nui Ba National Park. Based on criterion D of the IUCN Red List criteria (
<bibRefCitation id="70C0FF62B36E72AA7560FB083700BEDC" author="IUCN" journalOrPublisher="Science Press, Beijing &amp; Missouri Botanical Garden Press, Saint Louis" pageId="0" pageNumber="73" refId="B23" refString="IUCN, 2012. IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria: Version 3.1. 2nd edn. Gland, Switzerland and Cambridge, UK, [iv +] 32 pp." title="IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria: Version 3.1. 2 nd edn. Gland, Switzerland and Cambridge, UK, [iv +] 32 pp." year="2012">IUCN 2012</bibRefCitation>
), this species is qualified as CR. The new species is endemic to Bidoup-Nui Ba National Park, Lam Dong Province.
</paragraph>
